# Crude Oil Balance Sheet & Price Forecast Model

**Analyst:** Mohit Das | MSc Economics, GIPE Pune  
**Period:** Q4 2024 Actuals + 2025 Forecast  
**Tool:** Microsoft Excel

---

## About

This is a country-level crude oil supply-demand balance model built to
understand global oil market dynamics and their implications for India's
import bill. It was built the way an energy economist or commodity analyst
would approach it — structuring actuals first, then running forward-looking
scenarios with documented assumptions.

The model answers:

- Which countries are in surplus or deficit, and by how much?
- How has the global supply-demand balance shifted across quarters?
- What is a reasonable Brent price forecast for 2025 under bull, base,
  and bear scenarios?
- How sensitive is India's crude import bill to Brent price movements?
- Are OPEC members producing within or beyond their quota?

---

## Data Sources

**Supply-Demand Actuals:**
- [IEA Oil Market Report (OMR)](https://www.iea.org/reports/oil-market-report-april-2025) — global supply & demand (mb/d)
- [OPEC Monthly Oil Market Report](https://www.opec.org/opec_web/en/publications/338.htm) — member production & quota data
- [EIA Short-Term Energy Outlook (STEO)](https://www.eia.gov/outlooks/steo/) — Q1–Q4 2024 actuals and near-term forecast

**India Import Data:**
- [PPAC — Petroleum Planning & Analysis Cell, MoP&NG](https://www.ppac.gov.in/) — India crude import volume (~4.68 mb/d, 2024)
- RBI reference rate (USD/INR: ₹83.5) for import bill conversion

**Brent Price History (for base price calibration):**
- [EIA Spot Prices — WTI & Brent](https://www.eia.gov/dnav/pet/pet_pri_spt_s1_d.htm)
- Kaggle mirror: [Historical Daily Oil and Natural Gas Prices](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/prasertk/historical-daily-oil-and-natural-gas-prices)

---

## Model Structure

The workbook has five sheets:

| Sheet | What it contains |
|---|---|
| `Balance Sheet` | Country-level production, consumption, imports, exports, net balance, OPEC quota gap |
| `Quarterly Balance & Price` | Q1–Q4 2024 actuals + forecast; Brent price by quarter; India import bill estimate |
| `Scenario Analysis` | Bull / Base / Bear price forecast for 2025 with documented assumptions and probability weights |
| `India Import Analysis` | Sensitivity table — how India's annual import bill (₹ lakh crore) changes at every $5 Brent move |
| `Formula Reference` | Every key Excel formula documented with purpose and output type |

---

## Scenario Analysis Summary

| Scenario | Forecast Price | Range | Probability | Key Driver |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Bullish | $95/bbl | $90–$104 | 20% | OPEC cuts + geopolitical supply shock |
| Base | $83/bbl | $79–$88 | 60% | Current supply-demand maintained |
| Bearish | $64/bbl | $58–$70 | 20% | Demand slowdown + non-OPEC surge |

Base case assumptions: OPEC supply 25.84 mb/d, global demand 103 mb/d,
net balance −0.6 mb/d deficit, USD/INR at ₹83.5.

---

## India Import Sensitivity

At $83/bbl Brent (base case), India's annual crude import bill is
approximately **$142 billion (~₹118 lakh crore)**. A $10 increase in Brent
adds roughly **$17 billion** to the annual bill — a significant current
account and fiscal pressure point.

---

## Limitations

- Production and consumption figures are based on reported IEA/OPEC data,
  which carry revision risk.
- Price derivation uses a simplified linear elasticity model, not a full
  econometric specification.
- USD/INR rate is held fixed; currency movement adds a second layer of
  import bill sensitivity not modelled here.
- Forecast period is 2025; model should be recalibrated as new OMR/STEO
  data is released quarterly.
